<entry>
<author><name><![CDATA[tepples]]></name></author>
<updated>2009-11-20T07:44:18-07:00</updated>
<published>2009-11-20T07:44:18-07:00</published>
<id>http://forums.nesdev.com/viewtopic.php?t=5755&amp;p=52811#p52811</id>
<link href="http://forums.nesdev.com/viewtopic.php?t=5755&amp;p=52811#p52811"/>
<title type="html"><![CDATA[More than 64 sprites per screen?]]></title>

<content type="html" xml:base="http://forums.nesdev.com/viewtopic.php?t=5755&amp;p=52811#p52811"><![CDATA[
There are two bits in <a href="http://wiki.nesdev.com/w/index.php/PPU_registers" class="postlink">PPUCTRL ($2000)</a> that specify how sprites shall be rendered. They have three settings:<br /><ol style="list-style-type: lower-alpha"><li>All sprites are 8x8 pixel sprites, with tiles taken from $0000-$0FFF </li><li>All sprites are 8x8 pixel sprites, with tiles taken from $1000-$1FFF </li><li>All sprites are 8x16 pixel sprites made of two adjacent tiles, with tiles taken from both pattern tables depending on the least significant bit of each sprite's tile number </li></ol><br /><em>Super Mario Bros.</em> uses setting A; <em>Super Mario Bros. 3</em> uses setting C.<p>Statistics: Posted by <a href="http://forums.nesdev.com/memberlist.php?mode=viewprofile&amp;u=9">tepples</a> — Fri Nov 20, 2009 7:44 am</p><hr />
]]></content>
